There is a petrol price drop on Wednesday. Lower than the recent expectation. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Motorists are in for some major relief at the pumps from the first of April. The 95 unleaded is set to drop by R1,88 a litre with 93 decreasing by R1,76 cents. READ: Moody's move SA to junk status Diesel is expected to also fall by about R1,34 cents. While illuminating paraffin will decrease by R1,83 cents. eNCA's Devan Murugan has more in the video above